[h1]Type Selectors[/h1]

The most common and easy to understand selectors are [b]type selectors[/b]. This selector targets element types on the page.

For example, to target all the paragraphs on the page: [code format="css" codeId="509"]p {
   color: red;
   font-size:130%;
}[/code]
[note]A CSS declaration always ends with a semicolon, and declaration groups are surrounded by curly braces.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to give yellow background color to the element with id="intro", and black text color to the class="mytext":
[!raw!]
{0} {
   background-color: yellow;
}
{1} {
   color: black;
}

Fill in the blanks to create a style rule for all paragraphs belonging to the element with id="test":
[!raw!]
{0} {1} {
   color: red;
}
